    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but what if there isn't a \"new\" meaning? what if there isn't a second act? it feels less like a pause and more like the end. if the essence is gone, the rest of it—the breathing, the eating, the walking—it all feels so pointless. it's like trying to keep a house running when there's no one living inside anymore. why bother maintaining the structure if there's no soul to inhabit it?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
